summary: This is a travel voucher approval notification for a trip related to the U.S. v. Epstein case. The trip was for a witness interview in Santa Monica, California, from December 15-18, 2019, with total expenses of $2,227.40.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip Initiation
events.description: A trip was initiated for a witness interview related to the U.S. v. Epstein case in Santa Monica, California.

events.title: Witness Interview Trip Conclusion
events.description: The trip for the witness interview in Santa Monica, California, concluded.

keyFacts: The document is a travel voucher approval for a trip related to the U.S. v. Epstein case.
The trip purpose was a witness interview in Santa Monica, California, from December 15-18, 2019.
The voucher total expenses were $2,227.40 against an estimated trip cost of $2,440.58.
The document indicates ongoing investigative activity in the Epstein case as of late 2019.
The travel was processed through the U.S. Department of Justice's E2Solutions system.
